rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A system of implemented rules that specify how a software component will interact with other software components. Generally, an API is described in terms of the types of calls it will accept and the types of responses it will provide.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: API

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an API to the protocol by which users identify themselves, usually via a username and password.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Authentication Protocol

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that identifies APIs that are privately owned and not freely available.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Proprietary

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The system of rules for exchanging data that is implemented in the given API.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Protocols

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking an API to the individual, company or organization that has made the API available.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Provider

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an API to a website that makes use of the API.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the URL template, if any, that is used in making calls to the Internet API.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: URL Template

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Anyone who has written an Internet publication, e.g. a blog or a website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Internet Author
Author Category Label
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It's not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An Internet publication that has published articles by the given author.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Primary Publication

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An Internet author that is related in some way to the given Internet author.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related Author

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an Internet author to information about topics that the author has written about.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related Topic

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that stores properties that are relative to the combination of an Internet author and a topic written about by the author.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Author Topic Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of times that the author has written about the topic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related article count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The author that is part of the given author/topic combination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Author

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The topic that is part of the given author/topic combination.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related Topic

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A website or webpage consisting of dated entries authored by a single person or a restricted set of people, generally about a particular topic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blog

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a blog to the blogger or bloggers who are the authors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blogger

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.blog to the mso:book.article written for the blog.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blog Entry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a blog to the topic(s) or subject(s) of the blog.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Focus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a blog to the language(s) in which the blog is written.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a blog to the date when the blog came into existence.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Blog Started

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Anyone who is the author of a blog.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blogger

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a bogger to one of his or her blogs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blog

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A public profile on a social networking site, e.g. Facebook, that is created for fans to interact with businesses, organizations or celebrities.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fanpage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of users who said that they were at the physical location corresponding to the given fanpage, e.g. a concert venue.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Check-in Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of users on the given social networking site that have declared themselves fans of the given fanpage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fans Count
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use internet.fanpage.fancount_count instead (the expected type on this one is dated_float). DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[internet.fanpage.fancount_count]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of users on the given social networking site that have declared themselves fans of the given fanpage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fans Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of users who have communicated with or about the given fanpage within the week indicated by the timestamp. These communications include declaring oneself a fan, mentioning the fanpage in a post or commenting on the fanpage.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Interaction Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of check-ins plus the number of people who accompany people who check-in without checking in themselves.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: We're Here Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity type representing the collection of all internet forums. These are the online discussion sites where people can hold conversations in the form of posted messages.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Internet Forum

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A system of rules for exchanging data between devices or between software.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Protocol

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a protocol to an API that implements the protocol.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: API

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A webpage or website that is regularly updated with content, e.g. a blog.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Publication
Internet Social Graph Author
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: It's not clear what this type is intended to mean. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Relme Link
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It's not clear what this property is intended to mean. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A website where users can register, create profiles, and establish connections with other users of the site. Some prominent examples of social networks are: Facebook, LinkedIn, and Twitter.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the elements of a given agent that are members of a social network. For example, this type would be used to collect information about the number of people in an organization that are members of LinkedIn.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network Membership

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the change in the number of members in a given time period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Change in Members

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of agents that are in the given social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Members

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the number of profiles that a given agent has on a social network, e.g. the number of channels that a company has on YouTube.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network Use

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of profiles that the agent has on the given social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Profiles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the social network about which usage information is collected.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the profiles of a social network, a website where users can register, create profiles, and establish connections with other users of the site. Note that a social network profile is relative to a particular social network, so a single person could cover several social network users, one for each social network used by the person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network User

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that, when set to 1, indicates that the social network user is very active on social media, e.g. creating posts, responding to posts, connecting with other users, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Active User

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a user of a social network to a URL that establishes a connection between the user and any person who clicks the URL.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Add as Friend URL

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a social network user profile to an address associated with the agent who has the profile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Address
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use the following path instead: mso:internet.social_network_user.agent -> mso:event.agent.address. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:event.agent.address]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a social network user profile to an address line of an address associated with the agent who has the profile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Address Line
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use the following path instead: mso:internet.social_network_user.agent -> mso:event.agent.address_line. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:event.agent.address_line]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a social network profile to the person, group, organization or company that the profile represents.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to a dated number of contributions made on the given social network, e.g. number of posts, file modifications, responses, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Contributions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a social network profile to the entity that the profile represents.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Entity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to one of the profiles in the social network that is following the given user, i.e. being notified about the shares/updates of the given user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Follower Profiles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.social_network_user to the number of followers the user has. Followers are different from friends, in that the followers are not necessarily part of the user's social network. Please see mso:internet.social_network_user.social_network_size and mso:internet.social_network_user.following.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Followers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.social_network_user to the number of profiles on the given social network that the user is following. Followers are different from friends, in that the followers are not necessarily part of the user's social network. Please see mso:internet.social_network_user.social_network_size and mso:internet.social_network_user.followers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Following

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to one of the profiles in the social network that the user is following, i.e. being notified about shares/updates involving the profile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Following Profiles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a social network user to the number of items posted by the user on the given social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Items Posted

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a social network user to the last time that the profile was updated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last Updated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to the number of times that others on the social network have "liked" postings made by the social network user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Likes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to a URL that, when clicked, returns a list of all of the "friends" of the given user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: List Friends URL

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to information about the number of times that the user is mentioned on the given social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mentions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a social network user to an online group of which the user is a member.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Online Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a social network user profile to a city of an address associated with the agent who has the profile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Populated Place

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to a posting made by the user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Post

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network profile to the number of postings made by the profile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Post Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies whether the social network profile is viewable outside of the network
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Private

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.social_network_user to the number of users who have recommended the given user, e.g. as a workplace colleague.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recommendations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to a repository on which the user is collaborating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Repository

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a user of a social network to a URL that allows someone to send a message to this user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Send Message URL

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a social network user to the date that the user first created a profile on the given social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Signup Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network user to the identifier for that user on a given social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network Key

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.social_network_user to the number of members in the user's social network. This attribute is more in line with the concept of 'friends' on social networking sites, rather than the concept of followers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social_Network_Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking a social network user to the URL of the profile of the user on the given social network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Network URL

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking a social network user to a social network. A social network is a website where users can register, create profiles, and establish connections with other users of the site. Some prominent examples of social networks are: Facebook, LinkedIn, and Twitter.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Source_Social_Network
Specialization
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It's not clear what this property is intended to mean. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property indicating whether or not the social network user has been verified by the corresponding social network to belong to the person or enterprise that it purports to be.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Verified

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a social network user to the number of videos posted by the user.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Videos Posted

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a social network profile with an act of viewing the profile.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: View Social Network Profile

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a social network profile to the number of times that the profile has been viewed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Views

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The highest-level domain in the hierarchical Domain Name System used on the Internet. Specifically, it is the element after the final period in a URL, e.g. .com, .gov, .us, .ca, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Level Domain

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a Top Level Internet Domain to the type of domain, e.g. country code.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Domain Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a Top Level Internet Domain to the date when the domain was first used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Top Level Domain Introduced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an Internet Top Level Domain to the organization that assigns and manages URLs in the domain.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Domain Registry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a Top Level Internet Domain to the private organization or company that sponsors the domain. Note that this property applies only to a small set of Top Level Domains.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sponsor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a Top Level Internet Domain to its status, e.g. reserved, active or discontinued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Domain Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Organizations that assign and manage URLs in Top Level Internet Domains.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Level Domain Registry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a Top Level Internet Domain to the registry that is responsible for managing the domain.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Registered Domains

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Top Level Internet Domains that are proposed and managed by private organizations or companies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Level Domain Sponsor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a company or organization to the domains sponsored by the company or organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sponsored Domains

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Milestones in the lifecycle of a typical Top Level Internet Domain, e.g. reserved, active, and discontinued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Level Domain Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a Top Level Internet Domain to its current status, e.g. reserved, active or discontinued.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Domain Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A classification of Top Level Internet Domains, e.g. original domain (.com, .org, .gov, etc.) and country code domain (e.g. .ca or .us).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Level Domain Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a classification of a Top Level Internet Domain to all of the domains under the classification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Domain Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all websites. Websites are the sets of web pages served from the same domain name. Sites are usually accessible through the Internet or a local network by its URL, its uniform resource locator.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.website to its administrator. This is the agent responsible for the technical details of the site, including promoting and demoting moderators, database operations, and manage the site in general.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Administrator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a website to an API that is implemented on the website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website API

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.website to the mso:book.author that contributes content to the website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Contributor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of visits per day to the website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Daily Visits

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date that the website ceased to exist.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website Ended

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.website to the mso:language.human_language in which the website is written.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date that the website came into existence.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website Launched

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of visits per month to the website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Monthly Visits

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The owner of the website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website owner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a website to its parent website, e.g. Google.com is the parent of Google Maps. Note that this property does not apply to all websites.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent Website

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a website to a programming language that was used to create the website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Programming Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Websites that are related to the given website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related Websites

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a website to its current status, e.g. in development, alpha, beta, active, and defunct.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a website to its child website, e.g. Google Maps is the child of Google.com. Note that this property does not apply to all websites.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Child Website

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.website to the mso:media_common.subject covered by the site.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:internet.website to the mso:common.uri_template that the website uses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: URI Template
Website Owner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date that this person or organization became the owner of this website.

rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:common.ownership_relationship.start_date instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:common.ownership_relationship.start_date]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The person or organization which owns or owned this website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Owner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date after which this person or organization no longer owned this website. Reasons might include a transfer of ownership of the website itself, a merger or acquisition of the owning organization, or the taking down of the website.

rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:common.ownership_relationship.end_date instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:common.ownership_relationship.end_date]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The website owned by this person or organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:common.ownership_relationship.asset instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:common.ownership_relationship.asset]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Milestones in the lifecycle of a typical website, e.g. in development, alpha, beta, active, and defunct.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Website Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a website status, e.g. in development, alpha, beta, active, defunct, etc., to the websites that have this status.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Websites
